[b]Step 6:[/b]
in client.java, under:
[code]switch (skill) {[/code]
add this under it: (NOTE: u can add it anywhere as long as its under that method)
[code]case 14:
			sendFrame164(4416);
			sendFrame126("Congratulations! You've just advanced a "+name+" level!", 4417);
			sendFrame126("You have now reached level "+playerLevel[14]+"!", 4438);
			SendDialogue = true;
			if (playerLevel[14] > 98) {
				maxSkill("Mining", 2723);
			}
			break;[/code]
Explaining the code: [code]sendFrame126("Congratulations! You've just advanced a "+name+" level!", 4417);
[/code] Basically means that the "frame126" is telling the server to send the Mining frame that u have just advanced a level. 
[code]if (playerLevel[14] > 98) {
				maxSkill("Mining", 2723);[/code]
This tells the server what max level is needed to have maxSkill of mining. so the: [code]if (playerLevel[14] > 98) {[/code] is asking if player has of skill 14, level 98, would he have a max level?
the server says either no or yes, according to what the Maxskill is set to.

[b]Step 7:[/b]
add this in method:
[code]boolean addSkillXP(int amount, int skill) {[/code]

[code]int Mining = getLevelForXP(playerXP[14]);[/code]
Explaining the code:
this line of code is commanding the server to get the Level XPfor players in the skill 14 (mining) to see if they advance a level or not. if this command wasnt coded in, well, lets just say ur source will be fucked and u wont be able to advance levels :S

[b]Step 8:[/b]
